review_blob: dark almost black that shows red when held up to the light.  a thick light brown head leaves very little lacing, flavor is dark chocolate and alcohol with a bitter hops finish. the bitter aftertaste starts to taste like cigarette ash after a couple of minutes
mild aroma of wheat and cherry,  it has a foamy off white head that mostly dissipates  but leaves some lacing while it is there, a nice wheat flavor with cherries and a slightly bitter hops finish.
slightly hazy yellow with a white head that dissipates completely, very little aroma, the taste is overpowering lemon with a little bit of the wheat
Bottle. clear dark red brown color,  nice head that dissipates to a thin layer.  Wonderful sweet caramel and toffee aroma. Flavor is malty and sweet with toffee, and slightly bitter hops finish.
